  "title": "pagination: buggy first/previous/next/last logic",
  "body": "I feel like the logic used to hide/show the various previous/first/next/last links is buggy. Here are some screenshots:\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/11271018/a7396350-8ec3-11e5-8447-9bec6f94415a.png)\n^ I'm on the first page, everything is alright.\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/11271025/b2b4abb8-8ec3-11e5-846c-4ea1d8dd674a.png)\n^ I'm on the second page, I don't think the \"<<\" (first page) link is needed (redundant with \"<\" previous)\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/11271042/cc02a37c-8ec3-11e5-9191-16130d96d074.png)\n^ 4th page, everything is alright\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/11271048/d47b6d18-8ec3-11e5-8749-520d2570f62f.png)\n^ 5th page, oops the 6th page link disappeared. And I have both next and last (last might be useless here, and related to #594)\n",
